    pearls: ["The mnemonic for LAST symptoms follows a CNS-then-cardiac progression: perioral numbness → metallic taste → tinnitus → visual disturbances → seizures → unconsciousness → cardiovascular collapse -- recognize early signs and stop injecting immediately","Always aspirate before injecting local anesthetic and inject in 3-5 mL increments with aspiration between each to detect intravascular placement -- a negative aspiration does not guarantee extravascular position","20% lipid emulsion (Intralipid) must be immediately available whenever local anesthetics are used in doses capable of causing LAST -- the dose is 1.5 mL/kg IV bolus, repeat once if needed, then infuse at 0.25 mL/kg/min","Epidural hematoma after neuraxial block has a narrow treatment window: surgical decompression within 6-8 hours of symptom onset provides the best chance of neurological recovery -- new back pain with progressive weakness after neuraxial block is an emergency","The ASRA anticoagulation guidelines specify minimum intervals between last anticoagulant dose and neuraxial needle placement: enoxaparin 12 hours, rivaroxaban/apixaban 72 hours, warfarin requires INR <1.5, clopidogrel 5-7 days","Post-dural puncture headache is postural (worse sitting/standing, improved lying flat) and occurs 24-48 hours after dural puncture -- epidural blood patch is definitive treatment with >90% success rate"],
